```text
{1  Temp = Fact;
    Sat = FindRules(Temp,R);
    while Sat<>0 and Goal∉Temp do
    {2    r ← get(Sat); /* r: left → q */
         R = R \ {r}; Trace = Trace ∪ {r};
         Temp = Temp ∪ {q};
         Sat = FindRules(Temp,R)
    }2
    if Goal ⊆ Temp then exit("Success")
    else  exit("Not success")
}1
```

[Diagram: This is a forward-chaining inference loop: starting from known facts, it repeatedly selects applicable rules, adds newly inferred conclusions, and checks whether the goal has been derived. The process matters because it shows how rule-based systems can automatically reach conclusions from facts without backward searching from the goal.]

